#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.head.title:12-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\application_specific_voice_settings.htm+html.head.title:12-1"
msgid "Selecting a Voice Profile"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\application_specific_voice_settings.htm+html.body.h1:17-1"
msgid "Selecting a Voice Profile"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:18-1
msgid ""
"A voice profile consists of settings for the synthesizer, language, voice, and "
"other speech items that define how JAWS speaks. Traditionally in JAWS, users have "
"created specific language voice profiles, along with task specific profiles such "
"as profiles for proof reading, pleasure reading, and speed reading. Beginning with "
"JAWS 16, single profiles can now contain the settings for multiple languages, "
"allowing users to have a single task specific profile that works regardless of the "
"language they switch to."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:19-1
msgid ""
"For example, if a person spoke English, Spanish, and French, they can create a "
"single \"proofreading\" profile. With speech set to English, they would turn on "
"the announcement of all punctuation and set the speaking rate to be a little "
"slower than their normal reading rate. Next, they would switch the language to "
"Spanish, choose their preferred voice, and make the punctuation and reading rate "
"changes. After that, they would do the same for French and save their profile with "
"“proofreading” as the name. This proofreading profile can now be used regardless "
"of whether the voice is set to English, French, or Spanish."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:20-1
msgid ""
"As with previous versions of JAWS, you can set profiles to automatically be used "
"when you enter specific applications. For example, you may want a profile that "
"simply sets punctuation to “All” when your focus is in a coding application."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:21-1
msgid "The sections below describe how to create and manage voice profiles."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:22-1
msgid "Creating a New Voice Profile"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:23-1
msgid ""
"Starting with an existing voice profile is an easy and quick way to create a new "
"profile. You begin with basic voice settings, customize the settings to match the "
"activity to be performed or the application to be used, and then save the new "
"profile using a name that easily identifies it."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:24-1
msgid ""
"Before creating the profile, give some thought to how you want to use it and if "
"you want to use it in situations where you will encounter multiple languages. For "
"example, you can create a single voice profile that contains multiple languages "
"with unique settings for each language. With each language, you can choose among "
"the available voices you have installed for that language. For your native "
"language, you may be very comfortable with a very fast speech rate, but with other "
"languages, you may want to have the speech rate slowed down for better "
"understanding."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:25-1
msgid ""
"If JAWS detects language tags in a document or web page, it will automatically "
"switch to the appropriate language. If these tags are missing, you can always "
"press <strong>WINDOWS Key+CTRL+L</strong> to manually change languages. This hot "
"key opens the Select a Language dialog box. It shows all languages currently "
"installed on your computer."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:26-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Note:</strong> To create multi-language profiles, you must have different "
"synthesizer voices installed on your computer. These can be downloaded for free "
"from the Freedom Scientific web site. To access the latest Vocalizer Expressive "
"voices, choose the More Voices item from the JAWS Help menu."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:27-1
msgid ""
"You can also create a voice profile oriented toward a specific task or activity. "
"For example, you can have a voice profile dedicated to proofreading Word "
"documents, or a profile dedicated for leisurely reading of emails or web pages, or "
"a profile for software applications you use when creating your web page."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:28-1
msgid "To create a new voice profile, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:30-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\application_specific_voice_settings.htm+html.body.ol.li:30-1"
msgid "Press <strong>INSERT+J</strong> to make the JAWS window active."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:31-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\application_specific_voice_settings.htm+html.body.ol.li:31-1"
msgid ""
"Press <strong>ALT+O</strong> to open the Options menu, Press <strong>V</strong> to "
"choose the Voices submenu, and then press <strong>ENTER</strong> to open the Voice "
"Adjustment dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:32-1
msgid ""
"Select a factory voice profile in the Profile Name combo box. For example, "
"Vocalizer Expressive – (factory)."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:33-1
msgid ""
"Select a language in the Synthesizer Language combo box. For example, English – "
"United States or English – United Kingdom."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:34-1
msgid ""
"Select a voice in the Person combo box. For example, Allison Premium – United "
"States or Daniel Premium – United Kingdom."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:35-1
msgid ""
"Make any necessary changes to the speech rate, punctuation, or other voice "
"settings."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:36-1
msgid ""
"Choose Apply, and then No when asked if you want to apply these changes as the "
"default voice profile."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:37-1
msgid ""
"If you want to add another language to this profile, repeat steps 4 through 7, but "
"select a different language and voice, for example, Spanish – Spain and Monica "
"Premium – Spain. You can add as many languages as you have installed on your "
"computer."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:39-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Note:</strong> You can select a primary language for the profile. To do "
"this, see \"Selecting a Primary Language\" in the section below."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:41-1
msgid ""
"When finished, choose Save As and type a name for the new voice profile. Choose "
"Yes or No to make this the new default profile, and then choose OK to close the "
"dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:43-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Note:</strong> If you do not rename the new profile, it will use the same "
"name as the selected factory voice profile. However, its name will no longer be "
"identified as “factory” in the Profile Name combo box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:44-1
msgid "Selecting a Primary Language"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:45-1
msgid ""
"While setting up your profile, you have the option of selecting a primary "
"synthesizer language. This is the language that is heard when you activate the "
"profile. By default, this is set to \"Match JAWS UI Language,\" which means that "
"it always matches the language of the JAWS interface. For example, an English "
"version of JAWS will use English as its primary synthesizer language. A Spanish "
"version will use Spanish as its primary synthesizer language. For more "
"information, see Set Language as Primary in the <a href=\"../"
"the_jaws_application_window/Voice_Adjustment.htm\">Voice Adjustment</a> dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:46-1
msgid "To use a different primary language in the profile, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:48-1
msgid "Select a language in the Synthesizer Language combo box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:49-1
msgid "Choose the \"Set Language as Primary\" button."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:50-1
msgid "Choose Yes if asked to change the primary language."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:51-1
msgid ""
"Save the profile. JAWS now uses this selection as its primary language. It is also "
"identified as \"primary\" in the Synthesizer Language combo box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:53-1
msgid "Restoring a Factory Voice Profile"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:54-1
msgid "To restore a default voice profile:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:56-1
msgid ""
"Select the modified default voice profile in the Profile Name combo box, for "
"example, Vocalizer Expressive."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:57-1
msgid ""
"Choose the Delete Profile button and then Yes to delete the profile. JAWS switches "
"to the first voice profile in the Profile Name combo box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:58-1
msgid ""
"Select the Profile Name combo box again, and the profile appears and is identified "
"as “factory” in the list, for example, Vocalizer Expressive – (factory)."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:60-1
msgid "Deleting a Voice Profile"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:61-1
msgid "To delete a voice profile, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:63-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\application_specific_voice_settings.htm+html.body.ol.li:63-1"
msgid "Press <strong>INSERT+J</strong> to make the JAWS window active."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:64-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\application_specific_voice_settings.htm+html.body.ol.li:64-1"
msgid ""
"Press <strong>ALT+O</strong> to open the Options menu, Press <strong>V</strong> to "
"choose the Voices submenu, and then press <strong>ENTER</strong> to open the Voice "
"Adjustment dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:65-1
msgid ""
"In the Profile Name combo box, select the voice profile that you want to delete."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:66-1
msgid ""
"Choose Delete Profile and then Yes to delete the profile. JAWS switches to the "
"first voice profile in the Profile Name combo box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li.p:67-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Note:</strong> You cannot delete a default voice profile that is labeled "
"as “factory,” for example, Eloquence - (factory) or Vocalizer Expressive - "
"(factory)."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:69-1
msgid ""
"Select another voice profile in the Profile Name combo box, or choose OK to close "
"the dialog box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:71-1
msgid "Selecting a Voice Profile for an Application"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:72-1
msgid "To select a voice profile for an application, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:74-1
msgid ""
"Make sure that JAWS focus is in the application and then press "
"<strong>INSERT+CTRL+S</strong> to open the Select a Voice Profile dialog box. It "
"contains a combo box labeled Default, which assigns a voice profile that is used "
"globally by JAWS, and the For &lt;application name&gt; combo box, which assigns a "
"voice profile for a specific application."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:75-1
msgid ""
"If JAWS focus is in the Default combo box, press <strong>TAB</strong> to move to "
"the For combo box."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:76-1
msgid ""
"Press <strong>UP ARROW</strong> or <strong>DOWN ARROW</strong> to scroll through "
"the list of voice profiles, and then press <strong>ENTER</strong> to select a "
"voice profile. The dialog box closes and JAWS now uses the selected profile for "
"the open application."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Capplication_specific_voice_settings.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:78-1
msgid ""
"<strong>Note:</strong> If you select Use Default, which is the first item in the "
"combo box list, JAWS will use the same voice profile currently selected in the "
"Default combo box for the current application."
msgstr ""

